name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: I truly believe that even in the face of all that this year has thrown at us, that we are lucky to have family and friends we can count on to help us get through.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: This week as we prepare for an unconventional Thanksgiving celebration, it's important that we remember the strength of spirit that binds us together as Oregonians and as Americans.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: It's the spirit of our fellow Oregonians who may not have a warm place to sleep tonight but still maintain a fundamental kindness in their spirit, even when our society hasn't shown them that same kindness.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: It's the spirit of the firefighters and first responders who risk their lives to dig firelines as winds and flames rage around them because they are working to protect their community.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: It's the spirit of the small business owner who cut their own salary in order to keep an extra employee on staff because they live the ethos of their mission statement when they refer to their company as a family.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: It's the spirit of a young couple determined to get married despite not being able to have the wedding of their dreams because it's the commitment to each other that matters more than anything.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: It's the spirit of school administrators and teachers working to keep our students engaged in the virtual classroom while working from home, showing that they can adapt to a changing environment and still inspire the next generation.  https://t.co/rabEp0dyHm

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: Despite all of these hardships and all of these moments of trials and tribulations, I remain thankful for the spirit of my fellow Oregonians.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: Adding to the adversity, many communities in our state are still trying to put their lives back together after devastating wildfires leveled entire towns like Phoenix and Talent.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: Small business owners across our state have been forced to close or operate in a limited capacity for months, leaving their employees and their families (as well as themselves) in a place of uncertainty.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: --- forcing hard conversations and the postponing of important moments like graduations, weddings, birthday parties, and holidays.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: The year started with a once-in-a-generation global pandemic, which is still ravaging communities irrespective of borders, keeping many of us from friends and family we haven't seen in months ---

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: Today we give thanks.  There is so much about 2020 that didn't go the way any of us planned.  For many, this is a year that will forever mark some of our toughest days.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: There will be serious challenges on the road ahead, but let’s start by giving each other the benefit of the doubt--knowing that we all want the same things for our children and grandchildren.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: …and by making smart investments in our roads and schools and high-speed Internet to create jobs and make sure our people have the skills they need.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: As Treasurer, that starts by giving Oregon workers and families a chance to get ahead--by helping thousands of Oregonians plan for a secure retirement; by enabling young parents to open their child’s first college savings account...

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: Now it’s up to us to support each other. To be a part of rebuilding and coming out of this pandemic more resilient and stronger than before.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: The only way any of this is going to happen is if we put aside the divisions of this election and start looking out for each other. Oregonians have kind hearts and a generous spirit.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: We need to help those who’ve lost their job and may be struggling to afford rent or not have enough to eat.  And we need to keep planning for our future--helping put Oregon on a strong financial footing for whatever challenges come next.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: In the days ahead we need to help thousands of Oregonians rebuild their homes and businesses from devastating wildfires, no matter who they voted for.  We need to get control of this virus and help our schools and our economy re-open safely.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: But while it might feel good in the moment, this is no time for crowing about the election.  Just changing presidents won’t solve the many problems this pandemic has laid bare.  We’ve got a lot of work--and a lot of healing--to do.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: Tonight, as we look forward, I hope when all the votes are cast, we’ll be on the verge of bringing to an end this divisive presidency that has cost our state and our nation so much.  I believe that our country under Joe Biden will be a more decent, just, and hopeful nation.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: I also want to thank my opponent, @ElectJeffGudman, who ran a strong race.  I know his commitment to #Oregon is sincere, and I hope we can work together on the many areas where we agree. He made me a better candidate and a better Treasurer.

name: Tobias Read for Governor
tweet: I wish we could celebrate together tonight, so I could thank you in person for everything you’ve done for me and for our state. But for now, let me say thank you for the honor of serving as your State Treasurer again.
